      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>SCHEDULE L, PART V</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>ELIZABETH PHILLIPS IS THE TRUSTEE OF THE WAYNE E. PHILLIPS AND MARGARET M. PHILLIPS REMAINDER TRUST, FROM WHOM THE ORGANIZATION RENTS PART OF THE BUILDING AT 609 JEFFERSON. TWO-THIRDS OF THE SPACE AT 609 JEFFERSON IS USED FOR ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICES AND ONE-THIRD IS USED FOR PROGRAM SERVICES. THE BUILDING IS LEASED AT A BELOW-MARKET RATE. CLAIRE PHILLIPS CONSULTS ON THE CONTINUING IMPLEMENTATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ELECTRONIC MEDICAL RECORDS SYSTEM, WHICH SHE HELPED TO IMPLEMENT IN 2022. SHE HAS A PH.D. IN HEALTHCARE SYSTEMS WITH UNIQUE INSIGHT IN USING ELECTRONIC MEDICAL RECORDS FOR BETTER SERVICE TO PATIENTS AND CLIENTS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
